ility, and don’t ignore failures</li>\n <li>You’re focused on building systems that do something real, not just ticking boxes</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Bonus Points For</h3>\n<ul>\n <li>Rust or Go experience (used in parts of our pipeline)</li>\n <li>Familiarity with H3 and how to work with hex-based indexing</li>\n <li>Prior startup or small-team experience</li>\n <li>Any experience with threat intelligence, security, or defense data</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>You’ll like this role if:</h3>\n<ul>\n <li>You’d rather ship than theorize</li>\n <li>You like working on real-world systems, not toy problems</li>\n <li>You don’t need a big team or perfect process to be effective</li>\n <li>You want ownership, not micromanagement</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Compensation</h3>\n<p data-testid="paragraph-decorator" class="sc-beqWaB BGkvW">Competitive salary, meaningful equity, and the chance to work on something that actually matters.</p>\n<h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3>\n<p data-testid="paragraph-decorator" class="sc-beqWaB BGkvW"><strong>Who else works at Orion?</strong> We’re a small team of engineers and operators with backgrounds in F500, defense, and VC-backed startups. You’ll be working closely with Andy (CTO), Georgy and Shubhangi (Founding Engineers).</p>\n<p data-testid="paragraph-decorator" class="sc-beqWaB BGkvW"><strong>What stage is Orion at?</strong> We’re a Techstars and VC-backed dual-use AI company. We raised a strong seed round and are building the core platform and team now.</p>\n<p data-testid="paragraph-decorator" class="sc-beqWaB BGkvW"><strong>What’s the work culture like?</strong> We’re in-person in Denver 2–3 days/week. We move fast and prioritize momentum. Everyone ships. There are sprints where raw hours matter — especially when we’re pushing something critical. But we’re not here to burn out. We want intensity, not chaos.</p>\n<p data-testid="paragraph-decorator" class="sc-beqWaB BGkvW"><strong>What’s the interview process?</strong> 2–3 interviews. No take-homes. No leetcod