s, and resource needs to leadership and stakeholders.</p>\n     </li>\n    </ul>\n    <h2><strong>What You’ll Need To Be Successful</strong></h2>\n    <ul>\n     <li>\n      <p>Proven experience in a senior engineering leadership role, ideally as a VP of Engineering or similar, with a track record of managing and scaling engineering teams of 15+ members.</p>\n     </li>\n     <li>\n      <p>Strong technical expertise in modern software development, including architecture, security, compliance, and hands-on experience with technologies such as Python, Django, Golang, React, and Next.js.</p>\n     </li>\n     <li>\n      <p>Track record of delivering enterprise-level B2B platforms or SaaS solutions—ideally in a regulated or highly secure industry like insurance, healthcare, or fintech.</p>\n     </li>\n     <li>\n      <p>Demonstrated ability to lead in a regulated industry or a highly compliant environment is a plus, with a clear understanding of balancing technical rigor and business needs.</p>\n     </li>\n     <li>\n      <p>Exceptional leadership and interpersonal skills to build trust, motivate engineers, and elevate the engineering team’s visibility and impact within the broader organization.</p>\n     </li>\n     <li>\n      <p>Experience driving performance management, goal setting, and operational excellence in a fast-growing, high-growth startup environment transitioning from Series A to Series B and beyond.</p>\n     </li>\n     <li>\n      <p>Ability to pragmatically address technical debt and legacy system challenges while maintaining focus on delivering scalable, high-quality solutions.</p>\n     </li>\n     <li>\n      <p>Strong communication skills with the ability to engage effectively with executive leadership, product teams, and cross-functional stakeholders.</p>\n     </li>\n     <li>\n      <p>Willingness and ability to work onsite in New York at least three days a week, collaborating closely with leadership and product teams.</p>\n     </li>\n  