169	<h3><strong>ABOUT ZIPLINE</strong></h3>\n<p>Do you want to change the world? Zipline is on a mission to transform the way goods move. Our aim is to solve the world’s most urgent and complex access challenges by building, manufacturing, and operating the first instant delivery and logistics system that serves all humans equally, wherever they are. From powering Rwanda’s national blood delivery network and Ghana’s COVID-19 vaccine distribution to providing on-demand home delivery for Walmart, to enabling healthcare providers to bring care directly to U.S. homes, we are transforming the way things move for businesses, governments, and consumers. The technology is complex but the idea is simple: a teleportation service that delivers what you need, when you need it. Through our technology which includes robotics and autonomy, we are decarbonizing delivery, decreasing road congestion, and reducing fossil fuel consumption and air pollution, while providing equitable access to billions of people and building a more resilient global supply chain.</p>\n<p>Join Zipline and help us to make good on our promise to build an equitable and more resilient global supply chain for billions of people.</p>\n<p></p>\n<h3><strong>ABOUT YOU AND THE ROLE </strong></h3>\n<p>The Avionics team is a group of hardware, software, and test experts responsible for designing robust systems that control our life-saving drone delivery service in some of the toughest environments on Earth. Our team designs aircraft avionics that must excel in a wide range of harsh, real-world climates and electromagnetic interference (EMI) environments. The Avionics system is a vital part of the overall zipline aircraft system architecture, where we strive to achieve high performance and reliability while minimizing mass and cost.</p>\n<p>\n <br>\n You and our team will be responsible for delivering high performance communication and navigation systems that are tightly integrated into the aircraft and flight computer. These radio systems are at the core of a new unmanned aerial system that will enable Zipline’s impact to expand from 100,000 deliveries/year to 100 million across the globe. Zipline’s future success depends on the development of avionics systems that are low mass, low cost, high reliability, and produced at high volumes. Rigorous design engineering and validation is required, as well as ingenuity in approaches to packaging, integration, fault tolerance, and validation. We are looking for a test engineer with a strong foundation in RF fundamentals and prior experience with manufacturing test, design validation, system performance characterization, and certificaiton.\n</p>\n<p></p>\n<h3><strong>WHAT YOU'LL DO </strong></h3>\n<ul>\n <li>Own the design validation and test planning efforts for our RF products; including both design validation and manufacturing test.</li>\n <li>Develop a deep understanding of components under test becoming a subject matter expert in the component’s behavior under a range of environmental, performance, and system conditions.</li>\n <li>Coordinate cross-functional teams and external vendors to deploy high quality test plans and test systems in a timely manner to support production timelines</li>\n <li>Drive end-to-end test campaigns from development through design validation, certification, and production (often working all facets simultaneously).</li>\n <li>Triage and root-cause field failures, using data analysis, test heritage, correlation to operating conditions, and one-off test campaigns.</li>\n <li>Support the certification testing to enable our aircraft to fly in the real world.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>WHAT YOU'LL BRING </strong></h3>\n<ul>\n <li>3+ years of experience in RF engineering roles, with manufacturing test, system performance testing, certification, and design validation experience</li>\n <li>Bachelors and/or Masters degree in Electrical Engineering, with focus on RF Comms and Design</li>\n <li>Past test engineering e