244	<div id="job-description">\n <p><span><span><span><span><span><span>Senior Tech Lead &amp; Software Engineering Manager</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n <p><span><span><span><span><span><span>Schedule: Flexible Monday through Friday. Candidates may be remote, in-person, or hybrid.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n <p><span><span><span><span><span><span>Location: Candidates based in Baltimore, MD or willing to relocate to Baltimore, MD are preferred, but remote work is accepted. Occasional travel to conferences/clients may also be required. </span></span></span></span></span></span>\n  <br></p>\n <p><span><span><span><span><span><span>Who is Vectech?</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n <p><span><span><span><span><span><span>Vectech is a Johns Hopkins University spin out equipping professionals with the capabilities of a medical entomologist using AI and Computer Vision technology. Mosquitoes are the deadliest animals in the world, killing over half-a-million people each year. Lyme disease, spread by ticks, is now the most common vector-borne disease in the United States. There are thousands of different species of disease-carrying insects, which have different behaviors that call for different control measures. Vectech built IDX, an IoT imaging system, the world’s first AI vector identification system, with elements of a smart microscope, to assist vector control organizations with imaging, identifying and reviewing vector surveillance data, so organizations can take action and improve their impact. With Vectech's products, pest control organizations in public health can quickly generate the information they need to make public health decisions.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n <p><span><span><span><span><span><span>What will you do?</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n <p><span><span><span><span><span><span>Vectech is seeking a Senior Tech Lead &amp; Software Engineering Manager to lead our software team and work cross functionally with other technical teams (computer vision, systems, firmware, and entomology) to optimize cross-functional delivery and scale our products. You will work closely with other team leads, the Software Architect, Chief Technology Officer, product management, and leadership to resolve bottlenecks, introduce repeatable processes, and ensure that our cutting-edge technology is delivered efficiently using Agile practices, and engineering best practices. You will play a significant role in shaping the technology of Vectech. You will drive consensus with engineering teams to build foundational infrastructure at scale, and work with others to ensure it is used broadly and consistently. This role requires a background of understanding hands-on software development with leadership responsibilities, ensuring that our technical initiatives align with business goals and that our teams are empowered to deliver high-quality solutions.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n <p><span><span><span><span><span><span>Responsibilities will include:</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n <p><span><span><span><span><span><span>Technical expertise and hands-on engineering</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n <ul>\n  <li><span><span><span><span><span><span>Maintain technical fluency across full stack, mobile, and computer vision systems to support cohesive architecture and decision-making.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n  <li><span><span><span><span><span><span>Contribute hands-on when needed across firmware, backend, and application layers to accelerate delivery of critical features.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n </ul>\n <p><span><span><span><span><span><span>Process &amp; Workflow Improvement</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n <ul>\n  <li><span><span><span><span><span><span>Audit current workflows and implement scalable project tracking, sprint rituals, and handoff protocols across technical teams. </span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n  <li><span><span><span><span><span><span>Lead code review structure development and establish shared engineering practices across siloed teams.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n  <li><span><span><span><span><span><span>Lead by example in writing clean, maintainable code, and uphold coding standards through regular code reviews and mentoring.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n  <li><span><span><span><span><span><span>Establish unit and integration testing standards and frameworks (Automation and Git). </span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n  <li><span><span><span><span><span><span>Introduce knowledge management systems and ensure team-wide documentation compliance.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n  <li><span><span><span><span><span><span>Build systems with the long-term in mind, focusing on good design, robust testing, and sustainability from the perspective of cost and scale.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n </ul>\n <p><span><span><span><span><span><span>Cross-Team Coordination</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n <ul>\n  <li><span><span><span><span><span><span>Identify and resolve interdependencies between software, firmware, and CV teams.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n  <li><span><span><span><span><span><span>Serve as a technical translator between specialist teams and leadership to ensure shared understanding and alignment.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n  <li><span><span><span><span><span><span>Collaborate with and across Agile teams to design, develop, test, implement, and support technical solutions in full-stack development tools and technologies.</span></span></span></span></span></span></li>\n </ul>\n <p><span><span><span><span><span><span>Strategic Planning &amp; Resource Management</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\n <ul>\n  <li><span><span><span><span><span