246	<div>\n <p><strong>Overview</strong></p>\n <p>We are seeking a passionate and experienced Senior Structural Engineer to join our team in Washington, DC. The ideal candidate will have a strong background in structural design, with experience performing static and dynamic, thermal, vibration, materials, and fatigue analyses. This role requires a hands-on approach, the ability to design, develop and test structures for our satellite subsystems, and a strong team-oriented mindset.</p>\n <p><strong>About Us</strong></p>\n <p>At Magma Space, we’re on a mission to deliver the most precise spacecraft pointing ever achieved. We are developing groundbreaking control actuators, including magnetically levitated reaction wheels and control moment gyroscopes that drastically reduce onboard vibrations while delivering unmatched momentum. But our vision goes beyond hardware - we’re at the forefront of integrating AI-enhanced software for real-time environment monitoring with novel sensing capabilities. Our goal is to provide satellites with an unprecedented level of stability, agility, and accuracy, enhancing satellite capabilities like never before.</p>\n <p>We’re proud to be supported by NASA and the U.S. Space Force, and we’re now partnering with the Department of Defense on a RPOD (Rendezvous, Proximity Operations, and Docking) project. Across our efforts, you’ll oversee structural design, analysis, testing and more. Your first project will be in designing, integrating and testing a set of four advanced reaction wheels to enable rapid, ultra-precise spacecraft maneuvers for defense and scientific missions.</p>\n <p>Join us at Magma Space and make a lasting impact on the next generation of space missions!</p>\n <p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p>\n <ul>\n  <li>Lead the structural design, analysis, test and build of key components across our products.</li>\n  <li>Drive full-lifecycle product development: concept, design, prototype, test, and manufacture.</li>\n  <li>