256	<p><u><b>Job Description:</b></u></p>\n<p><span>DataRobot delivers AI that maximizes impact and minimizes business risk. Our platform and applications integrate into core business processes so teams can develop, deliver, and govern AI at scale. DataRobot empowers practitioners to deliver predictive and generative AI, and enables leaders to secure their AI assets. Organizations worldwide rely on DataRobot for AI that makes sense for their business — today and in the future. </span></p>\n<p><span>We’re looking for a Staff Software Engineer for DataRobot Generative AI platform. You will drive complex, cross-functional initiatives that directly align engineering execution with the company’s long-term strategic goals. You will be responsible for delivering scalable, maintainable systems that solve ambiguous technical challenges and create meaningful product and customer impact. Your work will help shape technical direction not just within your immediate team, but across multiple teams, ensuring smooth coordination and delivery of multi-quarter efforts.</span></p>\n<p><span>Your ability to execute with high reliability—producing robust, well-tested systems that measurably advance key business outcomes—is essential to maintaining DataRobot’s position as a leader in AI.</span></p>\n<p><span>Beyond technical execution, you will play a key role in mentoring others, fostering alignment across teams, and promoting a culture of continuous improvement. Your communication skills and ability to drive clarity through trade-off discussions, documentation, and knowledge sharing will enable DataRobot to scale its engineering excellence while staying grounded in customer and business value.</span></p>\n<h2><b><b>Key Responsibilities</b></b></h2>\n<ul>\n <li>\n  <p><span>Design and deliver robust, scalable internal platforms and services that enable fast, secure, and reliable software delivery.</span></p>\n </li>\n <li>\n  <p><span>Build automation that ensures microservices are secu