303	<div>\n <div>\n  <div>\n   <span id="docs-internal-guid-b5a44bdc-7fff-1557-33f0-82c81cfc638f">\n    <p dir="ltr"><span>Role</span><span>: Optical Engineer </span><span>Employment Type:</span><span> Full Time </span><span>Educational Qualification:</span><span> Master’s degree or higher in Optical Engineering or related field</span></p> \n    <p dir="ltr"><span>Work Experience</span><span>: Minimum 2 years of hands-on optical design experience in high-performance imaging systems, preferably in aerospace, defense, or precision instrumentation domains.</span></p> \n    <p dir="ltr"><span>Role Description</span><span>: </span><span>\n      <br>\n     </span><span>This role will be responsible for the design, development, and qualification of optical assemblies for Pixxel’s space-based spectral imaging systems. The Optical Engineer will contribute to every stage of the product lifecycle—from concept to deployment—and play a critical role in enabling daily, high-resolution imagery of Earth through cutting-edge satellite technology.</span></p> \n    <p dir="ltr"><span>Responsibilities &amp; Duties</span><span>: </span></p> \n    <ul>\n     <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">\n      <p role="presentation" dir="ltr"><span>Lead the engineering design and qualification of optical components, modules, and subsystems.</span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">\n      <p role="presentation" dir="ltr"><span>Collaborate with optical and mechanical engineers and scientists to convert concepts into validated prototypes and flight-ready systems.</span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">\n      <p role="presentation" dir="ltr"><span>Define and develop specifications for active and passive optical components and lead payload level and system level qualification.</span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">\n      <p role="presentation" dir="ltr"><span>Manage technical documentation and support procurement activities including RFQs, purchase orders, and vendor interactions.</span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">\n      <p role="presentation" dir="ltr"><span>Work cross-functionally with QA, development engineers, and supply chain to resolve design or quality issues.</span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">\n      <p role="presentation" dir="ltr"><span>Participate in technical design reviews and compile performance validation and qualification reports.</span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">\n      <p role="presentation" dir="ltr"><span>Travel, when necessary, for design reviews, manufacturing support, and quality inspections (domestic/international).</span></p>\n     </li>\n    </ul> \n    <p dir="ltr"><span>Desirable Skills &amp; Certifications:</span></p> \n    <ul>\n     <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">\n      <p role="presentation" dir="ltr"><span>Proficiency in optical design and simulation software: Zemax/Code V/Synopsys/ or equivalent and, ASAP/FRED/TracePro</span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">\n      <p role="presentation" dir="ltr"><span>Basic knowledge of detectors utilized in optical systems</span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">\n      <p role="presentation" dir="ltr"><span>Experience in tolerance analysis, GD&amp;T, and tight-tolerance optomechanical systems</span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">\n      <p role="presentation" dir="ltr"><span>Hands-on experience with optical metrology, environmental testing, thermal analysis, and space-qualified materials and adhesives</span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">\n      <p role="presentation" dir="ltr"><span>Familiarity with MATLAB, LabVIEW, or equivalent tools for analysis and automation</span></p>\n     </li>\n     <li aria-level="1" dir="ltr">\n      <p role="presentation" dir="ltr"><span>Strong communication and documentation skills</span></p>\n     </li>\n    </ul> \n    <p dir="ltr"><span>Candidate Acumen</spa