309	<h3><strong>About Zipline</strong></h3>\n<p>Do you want to change the world? Zipline is on a mission to transform the way goods move. Our aim is to solve the world’s most urgent and complex access challenges by building the first instant logistics system that serves all humans equally. Leveraging expertise in robotics and autonomy, Zipline serves tens of millions of people around the world.</p>\n<p>Join Zipline and help us to make good on our promise to build an equitable and more resilient global supply chain for billions of people.</p>\n<h3><strong>About You and The Role </strong></h3>\n<p>We are seeking a dynamic Metrology Technician with a passion for precision measurement. In this role you will play a crucial part in ensuring the accuracy and quality of our products using advanced measurement equipment, including the FARO Roaming Arm and Hexagon Bridge CMM. You will drive accountability to our designs internally and externally and collaborate closely with our design engineers and quality engineers to understand measurement capability and manufacturing capability of parts with complex geometries.</p>\n<p><strong>This is an onsite role based in South San Francisco.</strong></p>\n<h3><strong>What You'll Do </strong></h3>\n<ul>\n <li><strong>CMM Operation:</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<ol>\n <ol>\n  <li>Utilize the FARO Roaming Arm and Polyworks software to measure complex parts and components.</li>\n  <li>Create and maintain CMM inspection routines to meet stringent quality standards.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with engineering and production teams to ensure measurement processes align with product specifications.</li>\n </ol>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n <li><strong>3D Dimensional Analysis:</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<ol>\n <ol>\n  <li>Perform detailed 3D dimensional analysis on machined parts, assemblies and other components.</li>\n  <li>Identify and report deviations from design specifications.</li>\n </ol>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n <li><strong>Inspection:</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<ol>\n <ol>\n  <li>Conduct thorough inspections on parts, components and assemblies to ensure compliance with quality standards.</li>\n  <li>Document and report inspection results accurately, and initiate non-conformance reports when necessary.</li>\n </ol>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n <li><strong>Quality Documentation:</strong></li>\n</ul>\n<ol>\n <li>\n  <ol>\n   <li>Generate comprehensive inspection reports and maintain detailed records of inspection data.</li>\n   <li>Contribute to the continuous improvement of quality control processes and procedures.</li>\n  </ol>\n </li>\n</ol>\n<h3><strong>What You'll Bring </strong></h3>\n<ul>\n <li>Minimum of 3 years CMM programming experience</li>\n <li>Experience with Polyworks, Calypso, PC-DMIS, or MCOSMOS</li>\n <li>Strong knowledge of dimensional measurement techniques and GD&amp;T\n  <br>\n  (Geometric Dimensioning and tolerancing)</li>\n <li>Understanding of dimensional metrology concepts such as alignments, coordinate systems, measurement uncertainty, degrees of freedom, etc.</li>\n <li>Proficiency in interpreting engineering drawings and specifications.</li>\n <li>Excellent attention to detail and problem solving skills.</li>\n <li>Strong communication skills for collaboration within cross functional teams.</li>\n <li>Must be able to lift 35lbs</li>\n <li>Must be eligible to work in the US</li>\n</ul>\n<h3><strong>What Else You Need to Know </strong></h3>\n<div>The cash range for this role is $50/hr to $70/hr. Please note that this is a target, starting cash range for a candidate who meets the minimum qualifications for this role. The final cash pay for this role will depend on a variety of factors, including a specific candidate's experience, qualifications, skills, working location, and projected impact. The total compensation package for this role may also include: equity compensation; overtime pay; discretionary annual or performance bonuses; sales incentives; benefits such as medical, dental and vision insurance; paid time off; and more.</d