ze production processes. Provide real-time feedback to mechanical/electrical design teams to ensure assemblies are production-friendly and serviceable.</span></li>\n  <li dir="ltr"><b><strong>Customer Support: </strong></b><span>Provide exceptional technical support to customers by diagnosing, repairing, and resolving hardware issues. Collaborate with the team to address and resolve customer concerns related to production.</span></li>\n  <li dir="ltr"><b><strong>Reporting and Documentation: </strong></b><span>Maintain accurate records of production activities, processes, and assembly documentation, including schedules, inventory levels, and quality control measures. Prepare and present production reports to senior management.</span></li>\n  <li dir="ltr"><b><strong>Safety and Compliance: </strong></b><span>Ensure that all production activities comply with safety regulations and company policies. Promote a safe working environment by conducting regular safety audits and training sessions.</span></li>\n </ul>\n <p dir="ltr"><b><strong>Who you are </strong></b></p>\n <ul>\n  <li dir="ltr"><span>Autonomous and self-driven, with 5+ years of experience in hands-on assembly and repair of hardware products</span></li>\n  <li dir="ltr"><span>Familiar with production planning, inventory systems, and basic CAD and PCB tools like SolidWorks and Fusion 360</span></li>\n  <li dir="ltr"><span>Thrive and excel in a fast-paced, delivery-driven environment</span></li>\n  <li dir="ltr"><span>Organized and extremely attentive to detail</span></li>\n  <li dir="ltr"><span>Demonstrate excellent communication and problem solving skills</span></li>\n  <li dir="ltr"><span>Experience with 3D printing</span></li>\n  <li dir="ltr"><span>Understanding of mechanical and electrical engineering principles</span></li>\n  <li dir="ltr"><span>Must have advanced experience in soldering and troubleshooting electronic components</span></li>\n </ul>\n <p><b><strong> </strong></b></p>\n <p dir="ltr"><b><st